// Figure 6.1: Store Micro-Frontend Flow
// Host routing → Module Federation → Store MFE → API Gateway → Catalog Service → MongoDB

// ==================== ACTORS ====================
Browser [icon: chrome, color: blue]
Host Shell [icon: home, color: green]
Router [icon: git-branch, color: orange]
Registry [icon: list, color: purple]
Module Federation [icon: package, color: cyan]
Store MFE [icon: shopping-bag, color: teal]
API Gateway [icon: aws-api-gateway, color: red]
Catalog Service [icon: database, color: yellow]
MongoDB [icon: mongodb, color: green]

// ==================== PHASE 1: ROUTE DELEGATION ====================
// 1. Host Application determines route ownership
Browser > Host Shell : Navigate to /store
Host Shell > Router : Route analysis: /store
Router > Router : Match pattern /:appName/*
Router > Registry : Lookup config for 'store'
Registry > Router : Return Store config
// Config: { basePath: '/store', remoteName: 'store', exposedModule: 'ConsoleMicroApp' }

// ==================== PHASE 2: REMOTE MODULE LOADING ====================
// 2. Dynamic remote module loading
Router > Module Federation : Initialize for Store remote
Module Federation > Module Federation : Resolve remote URL
// Dev: http://localhost:4201/remoteEntry.js
// Prod: /remotes/store/remoteEntry.js
Module Federation > Store MFE : GET /remoteEntry.js
Store MFE > Module Federation : HTTP 200 (remoteEntry.js bundle)

// ==================== PHASE 3: MODULE FEDERATION RUNTIME ====================
// 3. Webpack Module Federation injection
Module Federation > Module Federation : Parse remote module manifest
Module Federation > Module Federation : Load shared dependencies
// Shared: React, React Router, Auth Context from Host
Module Federation > Host Shell : Inject Store module into DOM container
Host Shell > Store MFE : Mount Store application
// Pass appContext: { user, token, theme, apiBaseUrl }

// ==================== PHASE 4: STORE MFE INITIALIZATION ====================
// 4. Store application renders product listings
Store MFE > Store MFE : Initialize Store MFE
Store MFE > Store MFE : Setup internal routing
// Handle: /store/products/:id (product detail pages)
Store MFE > Browser : Render product listing UI

// ==================== PHASE 5: API COMMUNICATION ====================
// 5. Product data requests flow
Store MFE > API Gateway : GET /Catalog/products
API Gateway > API Gateway : Route to Catalog Service
API Gateway > Catalog Service : Forward to /api/v1/Catalog/GetAllProducts
Catalog Service > MongoDB : Query products collection
MongoDB > Catalog Service : Return product documents (JSON)
Catalog Service > API Gateway : Product data response
API Gateway > Store MFE : Product list (JSON array)
Store MFE > Store MFE : Process and render products
Store MFE > Browser : Display product catalog

// ==================== KEY COMPONENTS ====================
// Host: microFrontendRegistry.ts (route → remote mapping)
// Host: MicroFrontendApp.tsx (dynamic loader)
// Store: Module.tsx (exposed ConsoleMicroApp)
// Store: ProductList.tsx (product rendering)
// Backend: Ocelot Gateway (routing)
// Backend: Catalog.API (MongoDB queries)

